cs.DC, cs.AI, cs.SE, cs.SY, cs.PL 

Reasoning: 
- cs.DC (Distributed, Parallel, and Cluster Computing) is the most likely category as the paper deals with optimizing the performance of Stream Processing Systems (SPS) which are often used in distributed and parallel computing environments. 
- cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) is also likely as the paper proposes a Bayesian Optimization algorithm that leverages Gaussian Processes to iteratively capture posterior distributions of the configuration spaces. 
- cs.SE (Software Engineering) is another possible category as the paper deals with auto-tuning algorithms for SPS, which is a software system. 
- cs.SY (Systems and Control) is a possible category as the paper deals with optimizing the performance of a system (SPS) and proposes a method for tuning its configuration. 
- cs.PL (Programming Languages) is a less likely category as the paper does not focus on programming languages specifically, but rather on optimizing the performance of SPS through configuration tuning.
